Because, in $24!,
\begin{align*}
\left\lfloor
\frac{24}{3}
\right\rfloor&=8,\\\left\lfloor
\frac{24}{3^2}
\right\rfloor&=2,
\end{align*}and there aren't eight or more multiples of $9$ between $1$ and $24$, the exponent of $3$ in the prime factorization of $24!$ is $8+2=\fbox{10}.</think> <answer>10</answer>

